<div type="definition">
<p>SPEAK&gt;SPEECH COMMUNICATING a COMPLETE THOUGHT.???</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Cí 辭 was probably used as a technical term for a proposition by Mohist logicians, but in general the term refers to the formulation of a sentence.</p>
<p>2. Yán 言 refers to a public statement or a publicised saying.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>句 is colloquial modern Chinese for a sentence.</p>
<p>句子 is the regular modern word for a sentence.</p>
<p>語句 refers to the sentence as an element in discourse, or to a statement.</p>
<p>文句 (lit) focusses on the sentence as an organising element in literary composition.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
<div type="old-chinese-contrasts">
<p>LEIBNIZ 6.4 P. 135: S c i e n t i a est certa verarum propositionum cognitio.</p>
<p>P r o p o s i t i o est quae exprimit ex duobus rerum attributis sive terminis unum qui</p>
<p>p r a e d i c a t u m dicitur, in altero quem s u b j e c t u m appellamus contineri, ita ut cui</p>
<p>subjectum tribuitur, eidem et praedicatum sit tribuendum. Hoc autem exprimitur vel</p>
<p>absolute, vel conditionaliter, tanquam conse!quens" ex posita alia propositione quae 5</p>
<p>dicitur antecedens. Omnisque adeo propositio exprimit vel praedicatum in subjecto vel</p>
<p>[consequens in antecedente] contineri.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
